16/06/2003
TIRANA , Albania -- The interior ministers of Serbia-Montenegro, Albania and Macedonia met on Sunday (15 June) in Vlora, Albania, to discuss efforts to combat organised crime. The ministers also discussed co-ordinating a joint anti-crime platform prior to the EU summit in Thessaloniki. Montenegrin Interior Minister Milan Filipovic said that Montenegrin police will soon sign a co-operation agreement with Albania. (BBC, Mina - 15/06/03)
